{This song sent me back to secondary school. I was close to this one girl. I loved her company. She loved mine. But I didn't know what love was or what it meant. I overlooked it. She suddenly left school without saying anything to anyone. I never heard back from her. I got busy with school, university life and work. Recently I found out that she got married to a relative of mine. Now all grown up, I realised I was actually in love with her. I've never spoken to her since school. I know now that she's married we will never ever speak ever again. Things would have been so different for me had I known what love was. I cried. However as a Muslim, Islam teaches us that everything that occurs was destined by the Qadr of Allah, so not to have despair. What was never meant for you was not ever meant to reach you and what is promised will make its way at the right time. The one thing I will take away is to teach young people the true meaning of love. Not hookups and girlfriend/boyfriend, but to always be ready to find the one true love you will cherish for a lifetime. For that, one must understand what love truly is. Islam teaches love, so learn it â¤}

{"Channa Mereya" is a poignant and emotionally charged song that explores themes of love, heartbreak, and acceptance. Here's an in-depth insight into the song: Title: Channa Mereya Movie: Ae Dil Hai Mushkil (2016) Singer: Arijit Singh Music: Pritam Lyrics: Amitabh Bhattacharya Context within the Movie: The song is an integral part of the film "Ae Dil Hai Mushkil," directed by Karan Johar. The movie revolves around complex relationships and unrequited love. "Channa Mereya" is featured at a crucial point in the film, where the protagonist, played by Ranbir Kapoor, experiences heartbreak and reflects on the depth of his emotions. Musical Composition: Pritam's musical composition for "Channa Mereya" is soul-stirring and complements the emotional depth of the lyrics. The melody is haunting and beautifully captures the mood of the song. Arijit Singh's soulful rendition adds another layer of intensity to the composition. Lyrics: Amitabh Bhattacharya's lyrics are heart-wrenching and poetic. They express the pain of unrequited love and the acceptance of inevitable separation. The use of the metaphorical term "Channa Mereya" (meaning "My Moon") adds a touch of melancholy and emphasizes the emotional connection between the lovers. Key Themes: Unrequited Love: The lyrics delve into the theme of unreciprocated love, portraying the agony and acceptance that come with it. Sacrifice and Acceptance: There's a sense of sacrifice and acceptance of the inevitable. The protagonist acknowledges the pain but chooses to embrace it gracefully. Emotional Turmoil: The song captures the emotional turmoil of a broken heart. It reflects on the bittersweet nature of love and the challenges of letting go. Impact: "Channa Mereya" received widespread acclaim for its emotional depth, both in terms of lyrics and music. Arijit Singh's rendition struck a chord with listeners, making it one of the standout tracks of the film. The song became immensely popular and is often remembered as one of the most emotionally charged songs in Bollywood. Conclusion: "Channa Mereya" stands out not only for its musical brilliance but also for its ability to convey complex emotions. It remains a memorable piece of music that resonates with audiences who appreciate soulful and heartfelt compositions in the realm of Bollywood music.}

Lyrics have been beautifully crafted by Amitabh Bhattacharya and the song has been brought to life by none other than Pritam. Arijit Singh has voiced the track and the video stars Ranbir Kapoor and Anushka Sharma.  "Ae Dil Hai Mushkil" is a story about unrequited love.
